For further information on Homes England Frameworks visit the following website;
https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hca-contracts-and-tenders

The London Borough of Southwark has established a Framework for solicitors services for a period of 4 yearscommencing on 24th September 2018 at an estimated cost for Southwark of £9 million during the 4 yearperiod and an overall cost of £18-25 million including spend within this Framework from other participatingorganisations.
The framework is open to the following:
All London local authorities, details of which can be obtained from this link (http://www.londoncouncils.gov.uk/);
Companies wholly owned by London local authorities;
CCGs in the London area, details of which can be obtained from this link (https://www.england.nhs.uk/london/ccg-trust/);
London Fire Brigade (www.london-fire.gov.uk/);
London Councils; and
Local Government Association (https://www.local.gov.uk/)

The Riverside Group Limited wishes to enter into a framework agreement with a number of external law firmsto replace an existing framework. The term of the framework agreement, will be for 3 years with an option toextend for up to 12 months. The legal services are broken down into 4 lots:
- Lot 1- Property and Development;
- Lot 2- Non-property including Governance, Commercial and Employment;
- Lot 3- Corporate Finance and Banking;
- Lot 4- Housing Management.
Tenderers can submit tender proposals for any/all lots.
TRGL intends to appoint law firms to each Lot who are capable of providing high quality legal advice and whocan assist TRGL to reduce its legal spend. It is an objective of this tender that TRGL will achieve better value,enhanced service delivery and more efficient management of matters outsourced to external law firms.
